    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-05-28T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-05-28T06:30:00-05:00" n="302"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <head>302. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Iran</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d302fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_pol1">POL</gloss> AFG-<gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                            >PAK</gloss>. Confidential; Operational Immediate. Repeated to Kabul and
                        Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-05-28T15:00:00+03:30">May 28, 1963, 3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1038. I concluded telecon with <persName corresp="#p_SJM1">Steeves</persName> ten
                    minutes ago in which he reported that after two and a half-hours with Afghan
                        King,<note n="1" xml:id="d302fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJM1">Steeves</persName> reported on his conversation
                        with King <persName corresp="#p_ZSM1">Zahir</persName> on May 28 in airgram
                        A-522 from Kabul, June 2. (Ibid., <gloss target="#t_pol1">POL</gloss> 32-1
                            AFG-<gloss target="#t_Pak1">PAK</gloss>)</note> he was unable to move
                    him beyond agreement to give <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>s confidential
                    assurance of good behavior with Afghan wording reported in <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1035<note n="2" xml:id="d302fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d301fn1">footnotes 1</ref> and <ref target="#d301fn3">3,
                            Document 301</ref>.</note> “each side would endeavor to bring about an
                    atmosphere of good understanding, friendship and mutual trust” or to delete all
                    reference to the matter in the communique.</p>
                <p>On telephoning Foreign Minister for appointment to convey our latest information,
                    he told me that a few minutes earlier agreement had been reached as result of
                    another concession by <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>s to accept
                    confidential assurance of good behavior.</p>
                <p>There will be a joint meeting at five o’clock local time to finalize agreed text
                    of communique which will not be made public before tomorrow. <persName
                        corresp="#p_AA2">Aram</persName> elated and asked me to celebration dinner
                    this evening.</p>
                <p>I recommend immediate dispatch messages of congratulations on successful outcome
                    from President to <persName corresp="#p_ZSM1">Shah</persName> and from Secretary
                    to <persName corresp="#p_AA2">Aram</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
